The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Short stories on film
                                                                                                               Short stories on film
                              A still from Germanys Birdland, to be screened at the Kalpanirjhar International Short Fiction Film Festival                            
	The Seventh Kalpanirjhar International Short Fiction Film Festival, an annual event, will begin on November 1 at the Max Mueller auditorium. The five-day festival organised by Kalpanirjhar Foundation and Max Mueller Bhavan, Calcutta, is ready with 86 shorts from Germany, Spain, the UK, Austria and India, among others, selected from over 200 entries.        
	The festival will be unveiled by film-makers Buddhadeb Dasgupta and Mrinal Sen, followed by a screening of Desert/Exterior/Day of Germany directed by Mia Grau, expected at the festival. The 30-minute film about two actors who meet as strangers on a film set to play an intimate couple was shown at Cannes this year.        
	Several film schools, including the Hamburg Media School in Germany, FTII and SRFTI in India and Screen Academy of Scotland, are participating in the event. Films from more than 20 countries will be screened, including Belgium, Denmark, Poland and first-timers Mongolia and Iran, said Kalpanirjhar managing trustee, Sandip Ray.         
	The best fiction from India will receive Rs 20,000 from Patton, chosen by a jury comprising Swapan Mullick of SRFTI, activist and writer Jaya Mitra and film-maker Atanu Ghosh.         
	Shorts showcased at Filmfest Dresden will be the focus on Day II while films on the differently-abled, independent international entries, award-winning films from the US and a selection of short films from the Basque region are the highlights of Day III.         
	Childrens films will be screened on Day IV. Day V will show more shorts from film schools of India and Germany.                           MOHUA DAS                                                                                                                                                                   
